{
  "stem": "25027.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We were very close to the Soviet Union-- we were right on the border, practically.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And when you had a small radio, you could hear practically every country that was broadcasting in Europe.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Even London had a broadcast in Polish.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we had an idea.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And also, in 1937 or 1938, we suddenly had a visitor at home.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My grandfather had a sister who moved to Berlin in the early '20s, and they had a daughter who was born in Berlin.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they lived a wonderful life-- beautiful-- very well-educated, with centralized plumbing, and electricity, and theaters, and everything you could wish for, like you have in this country.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I'm not sure which year, 1937 or '38, she was thrown out of Germany, because she was considered a Polish citizen, because her parents were Polish.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Her parents died in Germany.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They were buried in Germany.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Before the war.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So considering the fact that she had nowhere to go, except her first cousin-- which was my mother-- and her sister Pepi, she came to live with us.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Just imagine the difference in life.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It's like taking a girl, a young woman, who was born in New York City, or in Washington DC, or in San Francisco, and throwing in to live in Iraq, or Iran, in a Third World country, or in Tijuana, Mexico.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "She died with my parent-- with my mother in World War II.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the discussions were many times between my mother and her.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Grandparents were old-- actually, Grandfather wasn't there anymore.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He died in 1933.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Grandma used to sit and listen.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They spoke German most of the time.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
